                    <span>This movie is becoming a classic to me.  It's funny, querky, dramatic at times.  I really like all of the key players who have these sil-ICONS down to a T.  Jobs is an ass and Gates is a dork but Wylie and Hall make them an endearing ass and dork. This movie is about a recent historical event that to me is uplifting and inspiring and a good notch in human history, an unfamiliar subject to the usual Hollywood crapfest.  Put it to a good mix of tunes from the 60's through 80's and you've got a pretty cool movie.  I could watch it hundreds of times and never tire of it.</span>
                  
              
